HEADWORD: Plumbous
<hw>Plum"bous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Plumbum</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or
containing, lead; -- used specifically to designate those compounds in
which it has a lower valence as contrasted with <xex>plumbic</xex>
compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

